```julia
function clean_column(col::String)
    return lowercase(replace(col, r"\s+" => "_"))
end
```

This function uses `lowercase` to make the column name lowercase and `replace` with a regular expression to replace one or more whitespace characters with an underscore. The regular expression `\s+` matches any sequence of one or more whitespace characters, including spaces, tabs, newlines, and other Unicode space characters.
